name: Nocturne
title: the Eternal Nightmare
lore: A demonic amalgamation drawn from the nightmares that haunt every sentient mind, the thing known as Nocturne has become a primordial force of pure evil. It is liquidly chaotic in aspect, a faceless shadow with cold eyes and armed with wicked-looking blades. After freeing itself from the spirit realm, Nocturne descended upon the waking world, to feed upon the kind of terror that can only thrive in true darkness.
blurb: A demonic amalgamation drawn from the nightmares that haunt every sentient mind, the thing known as Nocturne has become a primordial force of pure evil. It is liquidly chaotic in aspect, a faceless shadow with cold eyes and armed with wicked-looking...
allytips: Using Paranoia at a critical moment is well worth it even if you cannot use the dash.
Duskbringer isn't only an offensive ability. It can be used to close distance out of combat or escape from certain death.
Use Shroud of Darkness in tandem with Paranoia's dash. Your opponents may panic and waste a critical disable on your spell shield.
enemytips: Stay close to your allies when Paranoia is cast - there is strength in numbers!
Nocturne's Unspeakable Horror is broken with range, so try to save your movement abilities for when he casts it.

riot_spell_q.name: Duskbringer
riot_spell_q.description: Nocturne throws a shadow blade that deals damage, leaves a Dusk Trail, and causes champions to leave a Dusk Trail. While on the trail, Nocturne can move through units and has increased Movement Speed and Attack Damage.
riot_spell_q.tooltip:
Nocturne throws a shadow blade that deals {{ e2 }} (+{{ f1 }}) physical damage and leaves a Dusk Trail for {{ e3 }} seconds. Enemy champions hit also leave a Dusk Trail.

While on the trail, Nocturne can move through units and gains {{ e1 }}% Movement Speed and {{ e4 }} Attack Damage.

riot_spell_w.name: Shroud of Darkness
riot_spell_w.description: Nocturne empowers his blades, passively gaining Attack Speed. Activating Shroud of Darkness allows Nocturne to fade into the shadows, creating a magical barrier which blocks a single enemy ability and doubles his passive Attack Speed if successful.
riot_spell_w.tooltip:
Passive: Nocturne gains {{ e1 }}% Attack Speed.

Active: Nocturne creates a magical barrier for 1.5 seconds, which blocks the next enemy ability.

If an ability is blocked by the shield, Nocturne's passive Attack Speed bonus doubles for {{ e4 }} seconds.

Shroud of Darkness will remain active during Paranoia's flight.

riot_spell_e.name: Unspeakable Horror
riot_spell_e.description: Nocturne plants a nightmare into his target's mind, dealing damage each second and applying fear to the target if they do not get out of range by the end of the duration.
riot_spell_e.tooltip:
Passive: Nocturne gains massively increased Movement Speed toward feared enemies.

Active: Nocturne plants a nightmare into his target's mind, dealing {{ e1 }} (+{{ a1 }}) magic damage over {{ e3 }} seconds. If Nocturne stays within range of the target for the full duration, the target becomes feared for {{ e2 }} second(s).

riot_spell_r.name: Paranoia
riot_spell_r.description: Nocturne reduces the sight radius of all enemy champions and removes their ally vision in the process. He can then launch himself at a nearby enemy champion.
riot_spell_r.tooltip:
Nocturne reduces the sight radius of all enemy champions and removes their ally vision for {{ paranoiaduration }} seconds.

While Paranoia is active, Nocturne can launch himself at an enemy champion, dealing {{ damage }} physical damage.

riot_spell_i.name: Umbra Blades
riot_spell_i.description:
Every 10 seconds, Nocturne's next attack strikes surrounding enemies for 120% physical damage and heals himself.

Nocturne's basic attacks reduce this cooldown by 1 second (2 against champions).

wikia_skill_i1.name: Umbra Blades
wikia_skill_i1.blurb: Every 10 seconds, Nocturne's next attack strikes surrounding enemies for 120% physical damage and heals himself. Nocturne's basic attacks reduce this cooldown by 1 second.
wikia_skill_i1.description: {{sbc|Innate:}} '''Nocturne's''' [[basic attack]] is periodically enhanced, dealing {{as|120% AD}} {{tip|physical damage|{{as|physical damage}}}} to his target and to surrounding enemies, while also {{tip|healing}} himself for {{pp|15 to 40}} {{as|(+ 15% AP)}} per enemy hit.
wikia_skill_i1.description2: ''Umbra Blades'' can {{tip|critical strike|critically strike}} to the primary target dealing {{as|{{critical damage|10}} AD}} {{as|'''bonus''' physical damage}}.
wikia_skill_i1.description3: Basic attacks reduce '''Umbra Blades'''' {{sti|cooldown}} by 1 second, increased to 2 seconds against enemy champions.
wikia_skill_i1.notes:
* Basic attacks against structures will reduce ''Umbra Blades' ''cooldown but will not trigger the {{tip|splash damage}}.
* The enhanced attack will apply other [[on-hit effect]]s (only to main target) and can {{tip|critical strike|critically strike}} as normal.

wikia_skill_q1.name: Duskbringer
wikia_skill_q1.blurb: Nocturne throws a shadow blade that deals damage, leaves a Dusk Trail, and causes champions to leave a Dusk Trail. While on the trail, Nocturne can move through units and has increased Movement Speed and Attack Damage.
wikia_skill_q1.description: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Nocturne''' sends out a shadow blade in a line that leaves a ''Dusk Trail'' on its path, dealing {{as|physical damage}} to enemies it passes through and causing enemy {{tip|champion|champions}} hit to also leave a ''Dusk Trail'' behind their movement for 5 seconds.
wikia_skill_q1.description2: While on the ''Dusk Trail'', '''Nocturne''' is {{tip|Ghosted|ghosted}} and gains {{sti|ms|{{as|'''bonus''' movement speed}}}} and {{as|'''bonus''' attack damage}}.

wikia_skill_w1.name: Shroud of Darkness
wikia_skill_w1.blurb: Nocturne empowers his blades, passively gaining Attack Speed. Activating Shroud of Darkness allows Nocturne to fade into the shadows, creating a magical barrier which blocks a single enemy ability and doubles his passive Attack Speed if successful.
wikia_skill_w1.description: {{sbc|Passive:}} '''Nocturne''' empowers his blades, permanently gaining {{sti|{{as|'''bonus''' attack speed}}}}.
wikia_skill_w1.leveling: {{st|Bonus Attack Speed|{{ap|20 to 40}}%|Maximum Bonus Attack Speed|{{ap|20*2 to 40*2}}%}}
wikia_skill_w1.description3: Blocking an ability will double ''Shroud of Darkness' ''passive {{sti|{{as|'''bonus''' attack speed}}}} for 5 seconds.
wikia_skill_w1.notes:
* ''Shroud of Darkness'' has no cast time and does not interrupt ''Nocturne's'' previous orders.
* If ''Shroud of Darkness'' is active when '''Nocturne''' re-casts {{ai|Paranoia|Nocturne}} to dash to a target, it'll stay active until '''Nocturne''' reaches his target.

wikia_skill_e1.name: Unspeakable Horror
wikia_skill_e1.blurb: Nocturne plants a nightmare into his target's mind, dealing damage each second and terrifying the target if they do not get out of range by the end of the duration.
wikia_skill_e1.description: {{sbc|Passive:}} '''Nocturne''' gains {{sti|ms|{{as|335 '''bonus''' movement speed}}}} when moving toward {{tip|flee|fleeing}} targets.
wikia_skill_e1.description2: {{sbc|Active:}} '''Nocturne''' plants nightmares into his target's mind, dealing {{tip|magic damage|{{as|magic damage}}}} over 2 seconds and forming a tether between him and his target.
wikia_skill_e1.description3: If the target does not break the tether by moving out of range, they are made to {{tip|Flee|flee}} from '''Nocturne''' for a short duration while {{tip|slow|slowed}} by 90%.
wikia_skill_e1.notes:
* ''Unspeakable Horror'' has no cast time and does not interrupt ''Nocturne's'' previous orders.
* ''Unspeakable Horror's'' tether will not break if the target enters {{tip|invisibility|stealth}} or becomes {{tip|untargetable}}.
* {{tip|Spell shield}} will block the tether but not the {{tip|flee|fear}} from one already present.

wikia_skill_r1.name: Paranoia
wikia_skill_r1.blurb: Nocturne reduces the sight radius of all enemy champions and removes their ally vision in the process. He can then launch himself at a nearby enemy champion.
wikia_skill_r1.description: {{sbc|First Active:}} After a brief delay, '''Nocturne''' applies {{tip|nearsight}} to all enemy champions for 6 seconds.
wikia_skill_r1.description2: {{sbc|Second Active:}} While ''Paranoia'' is active, '''Nocturne''' can reactivate it to {{tip|dash}} {{tip|unstoppable|unstoppably}} to the target enemy champion, dealing them {{as|physical damage}}.
wikia_skill_r1.notes:
* ''Paranoia's'' {{tip|nearsight}} has no cast time and does not interrupt ''Nocturne's'' previous orders.
* ''Nocturne's'' dash and damage cannot be interrupted by crowd control but any effects he suffers during the dash will apply for their remaining duration (if any) after he hits his target.
* ''Nocturne'' will track targets that change locations (moving, [[dash]]ing, {{si|Flash|flashing}}) but not those that cover great distances ({{si|Recall|recalling}}, {{si|Teleport|teleporting}}) in which case he will dash to their previous location.
* ''Paranoia's'' {{tip|Nearsight|nearsight}} will prevent an enemy {{ci|Shen}} from using {{ai|Stand United|Shen}} on allies (regardless of having {{tip|sight}} of them or not) while active.
